article.headline: Richmond 69, Duquesne 66
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. (AP) -- Brian Morris' 3-pointer and a pair of free throws by Drew Crank lifted Richmond in the final 30 seconds to a 69-66 win over Duquesne on Wednesday night, ending an eight-game losing streak. The Spiders (6-18, 2-9 Atlantic 10) were up by as many as 12 in the second half and hadn't trailed until Duquesne's Gary Tucker made a 3-point play with 1:26 remaining. Kieron Achara's free throw with 47.7 seconds left capped a 14-0 Duquesne run and put the Dukes ahead 66-64. Morris scored 14 points and Dan Geriot added 12 for Richmond. Reggie Jackson and Achara led Duquesne with 13 points each. Leading scorer Robert Mitchell entered the night averaging 17 points a game, but was held to just five. The Dukes (10-13, 6-6) dropped their second in a row after a five-game winning streak.
